The paper discusses the use of machine learning methods to analyze and visualize interactions between attributes in data. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computer vision (cs.CV), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given the focus on machine learning and predictive modeling, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The discussion of visualization techniques also suggests cs.CV and cs.SI as possible sub-categories. Finally, the mention of redundancy and feature construction suggests cs.DS as a possible sub-category.
